@page "/about"
@model SpaceFlight_News_App.Pages.AboutModel

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}

@* Page Start *@
<div class="LightOnDark p-5 mt-3 mb-3 container">
    <section class="mb-4">
        <h1>About Spaceflight News App</h1>
        <p>This application is a development demonstration. It features full-stack development using modern programming practices. These features include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>ASP.NET Core using C# programming</li>
                <li>Server-side rendering</li>
                <li>Model View Controller &lpar;MVC&rpar;</li>
                <li>Razor pages</li>
                <li>MySQL Database</li>
                <li>Built using Entity Framework Core &lpar;EFC&rpar;</li>
                <li>Running on IIS web server</li>
                <li>DNS via Cloudflare</li>
            </ul>
    </section>
    <hr />
    <section>
        <h2 class="mt-4">SpaceFlight Articles</h2>
        <p>Spaceflight articles is a public API of news article metadata at <a href="@Model.SpaceFlightApiLink.Href" rel="external" target="_blank" title="Home | Spaceflight News API">@Model.SpaceFlightApiLink.TextContent</a></p>
        <p><b><time datetime="2026-01-26">January 26, 2026</time>:</b> Restricted data is now in place which allows only the newest 30 days of articles. This is a rolling demo, with new articles added to the dataset each day.</p>
        <h3 id="ArticlesSearch" class="mt-4">Articles Search</h3>
        <p>Search is a new feature with currently limited function. Use the search box to search the database, filtering by the media source. Submitting the search string refilters the page with only the articles matching the search term.</p>
        <p>The database has these news sites available to search for:</p>
        <ul>
        @foreach (var site in Model.NewsSites)
        {
            <li>@site</li>
        })
        </ul>
    </section>
    <hr />
    <section>
        <h2 class="mt-4">APOD: Astronomy Picture of the Day</h2>
        <p>APOD here is made available from a NASA data api called the <a href="@Model.ApodLink.Href" rel="external" target="_blank" title="@Model.ApodLink.TextContent">@Model.ApodLink.TextContent</a>.Today's APOD is provided on this website, and previous articles are not available to the public.</p>
    </section>
</div>
@{
}
